// Built-in bitmap font data for the retro graphics system.
// Provides two fonts:
//
//   Font 0: 8×8 CP437 (256 glyphs, 2048 bytes)
//   Font 1: 8×16 CP437 (256 glyphs, 4096 bytes)
//
// Each glyph is stored as N bytes (one byte per row, MSB = leftmost pixel).
// The CP437 character set covers ASCII printable characters plus the classic
// IBM PC box-drawing, block element, and special characters.
//
// Usage:
//   const glyph = font_8x8[char_code];    // → [8]u8
//   const glyph = font_8x16[char_code];   // → [16]u8
//   if (glyph[row] & (0x80 >> col) != 0)  // pixel is set

